body.p:
A 5-year-old, neutered male Shih Tzu was presented with a 2-week history of vomiting and
anorexia. On physical examination, there were no abnormal findings including on auscultation.
The dog’s complete blood count and serum chemistry were within the reference ranges, except
for hepatic enzymes, such as alanine aminotransferase (968 U/l; reference
range, 19–100 U/l), gamma-glutamyl transferase (22 U/l;
reference range, 0–6 U/l), alkaline phosphatase (280 U/l;
reference range, 15–127 U/l) and ammonia (143 µmol;
reference range, 0–98 µmol).
